# 🧮 Simple Python Calculator

A simple command-line calculator built with Python.  
It supports **addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, percentage**, and also has an option to quit.

---

## 🚀 Features
- ➕ Addition
- ➖ Subtraction
-  ✖ Multiplication
- ➗ Division
- 📊 Percentage calculation (`a` is percentage of `b`)
- ❌ Quit anytime (either before entering numbers or during operations)

---

## ⚙️ Requirements
- Python 3.10 or higher (because we used `match-case`)

---

## 📥 Installation
1. Clone this repository (or download the code):
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/tanujsingh53/python-calculator.git


cd python-calculator


▶️ How to Run

Run the program using:

python calculator.py

💡 Usage Example
Enter the first number (or q to quit): 20
Enter the second number (or q to quit): 80

What kind of operation you want to perform.
Press + for addition
Press - for subtraction
Press / for division
Press * for multiplication
Press % for percentage (a out of b)
Press q to quit

Enter Operation : %
20 is 25.00% of 80

📌 Notes

If invalid input is entered (like text instead of a number), the program will handle it gracefully.

You can exit anytime by typing q.

